A fine combination of horrible and sweet; I love the art and music. The adventure itself (puzzles, etc.) is pretty good--very good for a mobile game. The puzzles are sometimes too hard for casual gaming but you can easily find hints online. Highly recommended--as long as you're not too easily shocked. Split into parts for the play store, which works well: after the first part you know what you're getting and can choose whether to pay more.
